      "id": 1191,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:27",
      "content": "Your orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-27-auto-restart-settings`. Commit your changes. Do not push.\n\nChange `SYNAPSE_AUTO_RESTART_TASKS` from an env var to a `.synapse/settings.json` setting.\n\nThe settings file is at `.synapse/settings.json` (same file that already stores `theme`, etc.). It's read by the dashboard and the MCP server.\n\n---\n\n## Change 1 — src/db.ts: expose a readSettings helper (if not already available)\n\nCheck if there's already a `readSettings()` function exported from `src/db.ts` or `src/dashboard.ts`. If not, add a simple one to `src/db.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport function readSynapseSettings(): Record<string, unknown> {\n  const settingsPath = join(process.cwd(), '.synapse', 'settings.json');\n  try {\n    const { existsSync, readFileSync } = require('fs');  // use static import form\n    if (existsSync(settingsPath)) return JSON.parse(readFileSync(settingsPath, 'utf8'));\n  } catch {}\n  return {};\n}\n```\n\nActually, check `src/dashboard.ts` — it already has a `readSettings()` function (local to dashboard). If it's not exported, add an equivalent export to `src/db.ts` that reads the same `.synapse/settings.json` file.\n\n---\n\n## Change 2 — src/mcp-server.ts: read threshold from settings\n\nReplace:\n```typescript\nconst AUTO_RESTART_AFTER_TASKS = parseInt(process.env.SYNAPSE_AUTO_RESTART_TASKS ?? '5', 10);\n```\n\nWith:\n```typescript\nconst settings = readSynapseSettings();  // import from ./db.js\nconst AUTO_RESTART_AFTER_TASKS = typeof settings.autoRestartTasks === 'number'\n  ? settings.autoRestartTasks\n  : 5;\n```\n\nThe setting key is `autoRestartTasks` (camelCase, matches the existing settings convention). Default is 5 if not set.\n\n---\n\n## Change 3 — src/dashboard.ts: expose settings endpoint for this field\n\nThe existing `POST /api/settings` endpoint already accepts arbitrary key-value merges, so no new endpoint needed. But add `autoRestartTasks` to `GET /api/settings` response — it's already included since the endpoint returns all settings. No code change needed here; just verify that `POST /api/settings` with `{ \"autoRestartTasks\": 10 }` would work (it should — the existing merge logic handles it).\n\nAlso update the restart handler in `src/dashboard.ts` to read from settings instead of env var:\n```typescript\nconst settings = readSettings(); // local function already exists\nconst AUTO_RESTART_AFTER_TASKS = typeof settings.autoRestartTasks === 'number' ? settings.autoRestartTasks : 5;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Change 4 — Remove env var support\n\nRemove any remaining `process.env.SYNAPSE_AUTO_RESTART_TASKS` references.\n\n---\n\nBuild `npm run build` and verify clean.\n",
